	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=844><span id= >Galuvyen</span></a><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.67]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>From an RP standpoint, illusions shouldn't give any stats at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;An illusion is making yourself look like something, not turning yourself into something.  Shamans, druids, and necromancers get the real nice effects because they are actually turning into a bear/wolf/tree/skeleton or whatever they happen to be turning into.  I never really understood why an illusion would grant any special effects.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>34th Mage of Cazic-Thule<br>Member of The Chosen Elite<br>25th Druid of The Nameless<br></td></tr>
